title: Grateful Dead Live at Uptown Theater on 1978-01-30
description: Promised Land, Dire Wolf, Mexicali Blues-> Big River, Brown Eyed Women, Looks Like Rain, Peggy-O, It's All Over Now, Deal, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication Bertha-> Good Lovin', Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Stella Blue-> Franklin's Tower-> Around & Around, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: pretty good sounds good for an aud. you can hear a bit of echo but its not bad at all
little gem Check out the awesome energy and scorching lead guitar work on the Lazy Lighting-Supplication.  Yes!

Funny Just about any show they bust out Franklin's towards the end of the show is a ripper. This one is no exception, sound could be a little better, but it's still quite listenable. The show really starts with the BE Women, a bit subdued before that.....
uptown theater i love this show in chicago.Jerry just takes over in the supplication during lazy lighting."wow".great show

As good an AUD as you can generally expect The show has its incandescent moments, but is marred by the characteristic 78 laziness and off-key, over-the-top silliness. 

When I listened to the first show of 1978, I thought, Wow, maybe January was a better than average month for this year. Not so much. It's like they blew most of their mojo-wad for the entire year on that one show.
